  <front>
   <head>SONNET VII.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">C**e, with whom, my pilot and my guide,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Pleas'd I have travers'd thy Sabrina's flood,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Both where she foams impetuous soil'd with mud,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And where she peaceful rolls her golden tide.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Never, O never let ambition's pride</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">(Too oft pretexted with our country's good)</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And tinsel'd pomp, despis'd when understood,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or thirst of wealth thee from her banks divide.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Reflect how calmly, like her infant wave,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Flows the clear current of a private life;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">See the wide publick stream by tempests toss'd,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Of ev'ry changing wind the sport, or slave,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Soil'd with corruption, vex'd with party strife,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Cover'd with wrecks of peace and honour lost.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
